Author: TonyL#3577
Content:
If you want to tail daemon logs you may use something like a 
`tail -f ~/.komodo/debug.log`

Author: TonyL#3577
Content: Or `tail -f ~/.komodo/%assetchainname%/debug.log` for a specific assetchain daemon

start komodod with daemon param, if you want to run daemon in bg, and can execute wallet commands

`komodod -daemon`

Author: JUR4J79#4798
Content:
Hi everyone, I've been using this KomodoWallet for macOS: https://github.com/SuperNETorg/komodoWallet

But now it cannot launch, it is stucked on the loading screen. For hours. I found the blogpost about mandatory komodo blockchain upgrade from Aug 27. I understand that this wallet was not updated for a year and that's why it cannot connect.

So I downloaded Agama wallet, setup a new KMD wallet. But, there is no option to import private key from my previous (mentioned) wallet. Yes, I've backed up my private keys.

How do I sweep my old wallet into Agama? What will happen to my interest that accumulated in the old wallet? When I check my address on KMD block explorer, there is only original amount without the interest.

Author: SHossain#0007
Content: @JUR4J79 click on the **Import key** and enter your passphrase or privkey to import

Author: SHossain#0007
Content: if you have your privkey you can login and access your funds using the privkey

Author: JUR4J79#4798
Content: @SHossain There is no such option, only wallets tab

Author: SHossain#0007
Content: did you start native mode or lite mode?

Author: JUR4J79#4798
Content: lite

Author: SHossain#0007
Content: then, you can't import privkey in that mode. but, you can use your privkey to login

Author: SHossain#0007
Content: you can only import privkeys in native mode

Author: JUR4J79#4798
Content: Ok, I've switched to native mode and now waiting for blockchain to sync

Author: JUR4J79#4798
Content: What about interest from previous wallet?

Author: JUR4J79#4798
Content: Is it gone?

Author: JUR4J79#4798
Content: that's strange, probably agama found the old komodo wallet.dat and imported it automatically

Author: JUR4J79#4798
Content: because now i see it

Author: JUR4J79#4798
Content: also with interest

Author: SHossain#0007
Content: once the chain is fully synced you will see your balance and reward

Author: JUR4J79#4798
Content: great, thanks @SHossain
